-- China Deaths From Flooding Reach 107, More Rainfall Expected, Xinhua Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-13T14:29:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/china-deaths-from-flooding-reach-107-more-rainfall-expected-xinhua-says.html

          
          
             Flooding from heavy rains in China
have left 107 people dead and 59 missing across the country,
mostly in areas along the Yangtze River, the official Xinhua
News Agency said today citing the Ministry of Civil Affairs.  
 Rain-triggered floods had affected some 29 million people
and 997,000 have been evacuated, said Xinhua, citing data from
the ministry as of 4 p.m. Tuesday afternoon.  
 The China Meteorological Administration forecast that
rainstorms would continue to soak some flooded regions in the
provinces of Guizhou, Sichuan, Hubei, Jiangsu, Zhejiang and
Anhui and downpours are also expected in Chongqing Municipality
over the next three days, Xinhua said.  
          
          


  


        